{
  "video_id": "ZWfCi9WxK1E",
  "title": "A young poet tells the story of Darfur | Emtithal Mahmoud",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12814.0,
      "end_time": 16931.0,
      "text": "I was 10 years old when I learned what the word \"genocide\" meant."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 18575.0,
      "end_time": 20279.0,
      "text": "It was 2003,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 20303.0,
      "end_time": 24405.0,
      "text": "and my people were being brutally attacked because of their race --"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 24429.0,
      "end_time": 26232.0,
      "text": "hundreds of thousands murdered,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 26257.0,
      "end_time": 28205.0,
      "text": "millions displaced,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 28229.0,
      "end_time": 31528.0,
      "text": "a nation torn apart at the hands of its own government."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 32189.999999999996,
      "end_time": 36208.0,
      "text": "My mother and father immediately began speaking out against the crisis."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 36233.0,
      "end_time": 37718.0,
      "text": "I didn&#39;t really understand it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 37743.0,
      "end_time": 40589.0,
      "text": "except for the fact that it was destroying my parents."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 41211.0,
      "end_time": 44924.0,
      "text": "One day, I walked in on my mother crying,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 44948.0,
      "end_time": 49595.0,
      "text": "and I asked her why we are burying so many people."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 50220.0,
      "end_time": 52923.0,
      "text": "I don&#39;t remember the words that she chose"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 52947.0,
      "end_time": 57184.0,
      "text": "to describe genocide to her 10-year-old daughter,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 57208.0,
      "end_time": 58836.0,
      "text": "but I remember the feeling."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 59561.0,
      "end_time": 62616.0,
      "text": "We felt completely alone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 62640.0,
      "end_time": 64558.0,
      "text": "as if no one could hear us,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 64581.0,
      "end_time": 67390.0,
      "text": "as if we were essentially invisible."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 68179.0,
      "end_time": 72208.0,
      "text": "This is when I wrote my first poem about Darfur."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 72964.0,
      "end_time": 77952.0,
      "text": "I wrote poetry to convince people to hear and see us,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 77976.0,
      "end_time": 80446.0,
      "text": "and that&#39;s how I learned the thing that changed me."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 81111.0,
      "end_time": 82907.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s easy to be seen."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 82931.0,
      "end_time": 88410.0,
      "text": "I mean, look at me -- I&#39;m a young African woman with a scarf around my head,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 88650.0,
      "end_time": 90228.0,
      "text": "an American accent on my tongue"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 90252.0,
      "end_time": 94610.0,
      "text": "and a story that makes even the most brutal of Monday mornings seem inviting."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 95851.0,
      "end_time": 99454.0,
      "text": "But it&#39;s hard to convince people that they deserve to be seen."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 100561.0,
      "end_time": 102972.0,
      "text": "I learned this in my high school classroom one day,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 102996.0,
      "end_time": 105871.0,
      "text": "when my teacher asked me to give a presentation about Darfur."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 105895.0,
      "end_time": 109789.0,
      "text": "I was setting up the projector when a classmate of mine said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 109814.0,
      "end_time": 111908.0,
      "text": "\"Why do you have to talk about this?"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 111933.0,
      "end_time": 114983.0,
      "text": "Can&#39;t you think about us and how it will make us feel?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 115700.0,
      "end_time": 117147.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 117171.0,
      "end_time": 121235.0,
      "text": "My 14-year-old self didn&#39;t know what to say to her,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 121259.0,
      "end_time": 125121.0,
      "text": "or how to explain the pain that I felt in that moment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 125145.0,
      "end_time": 129216.0,
      "text": "and in every moment that we were forced not to talk about \"this.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 129240.00000000001,
      "end_time": 134840.0,
      "text": "Her words took me back to the days and nights on the ground in Darfur,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 134108.0,
      "end_time": 136562.0,
      "text": "where we were forced to remain silent;"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 136586.0,
      "end_time": 138777.0,
      "text": "where we didn&#39;t speak over morning tea"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 138801.0,
      "end_time": 143254.0,
      "text": "because the warplanes overhead would swallow any and all noise;"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 143278.0,
      "end_time": 145400.0,
      "text": "back to the days when we were told"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 145425.0,
      "end_time": 148214.0,
      "text": "not only that we don&#39;t deserve to be heard"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 148238.0,
      "end_time": 151540.0,
      "text": "but that we do not have a right to exist."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 151783.0,
      "end_time": 154262.0,
      "text": "And this is where the magic happened,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 154286.0,
      "end_time": 157509.0,
      "text": "in that classroom when all the students started taking their seats"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 157533.0,
      "end_time": 158802.0,
      "text": "and I began to speak,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 158826.0,
      "end_time": 162565.0,
      "text": "despite this renewed feeling that I didn&#39;t deserve to be there,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 162589.0,
      "end_time": 164290.0,
      "text": "that I didn&#39;t belong there"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 164530.0,
      "end_time": 166430.0,
      "text": "or have a right to break the silence."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 166930.0,
      "end_time": 168614.0,
      "text": "As I talked,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 168638.0,
      "end_time": 171281.0,
      "text": "and my classmates listened,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 171305.0,
      "end_time": 172775.0,
      "text": "the fear ebbed away."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 173842.0,
      "end_time": 175419.0,
      "text": "My mind became calm,"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 175443.0,
      "end_time": 177120.0,
      "text": "and I felt safe."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 178616.0,
      "end_time": 181513.0,
      "text": "It was the sound of our grieving,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 181537.0,
      "end_time": 184260.0,
      "text": "the feel of their arms around me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 184284.0,
      "end_time": 186565.0,
      "text": "the steady walls that held us together."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 187746.0,
      "end_time": 189677.0,
      "text": "It felt nothing like a vacuum."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 190621.0,
      "end_time": 193897.0,
      "text": "I choose poetry because it&#39;s so visceral."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 194641.0,
      "end_time": 197951.0,
      "text": "When someone is standing in front of you, mind, body and soul,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 197975.0,
      "end_time": 199176.0,
      "text": "saying \"Witness me,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 199200.0,
      "end_time": 203130.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s impossible not to become keenly aware of your own humanity."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 203413.0,
      "end_time": 205213.0,
      "text": "This changed everything for me."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 205237.0,
      "end_time": 206783.0,
      "text": "It gave me courage."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 207703.0,
      "end_time": 210294.0,
      "text": "Every day I experience the power of witness,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 210318.0,
      "end_time": 212419.0,
      "text": "and because of that, I am whole."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 212443.0,
      "end_time": 213925.0,
      "text": "And so now I ask:"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 213949.0,
      "end_time": 215315.0,
      "text": "Will you witness me?"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 217221.0,
      "end_time": 219255.0,
      "text": "They hand me the microphone"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 219279.0,
      "end_time": 222579.0,
      "text": "as my shoulders sink under the weight of this stress."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 224163.0,
      "end_time": 226121.0,
      "text": "The woman says,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 226145.0,
      "end_time": 228586.0,
      "text": "\"The one millionth refugee just left South Sudan."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 228610.0,
      "end_time": 230670.0,
      "text": "Can you comment?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 230910.0,
      "end_time": 234111.0,
      "text": "I feel my feet rock back and forth on the heels my mother bought,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 234135.0,
      "end_time": 235313.0,
      "text": "begging the question:"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 235337.0,
      "end_time": 238870.0,
      "text": "Do we stay, or is it safer to choose flight?"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 238646.0,
      "end_time": 240897.0,
      "text": "My mind echoes the numbers:"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 241561.0,
      "end_time": 243224.0,
      "text": "one million gone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 243248.0,
      "end_time": 244870.0,
      "text": "two million displaced,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 244894.0,
      "end_time": 247614.0,
      "text": "400,000 dead in Darfur."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 247638.0,
      "end_time": 249344.0,
      "text": "And this lump takes over my throat,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 249368.0,
      "end_time": 251990.0,
      "text": "as if each of those bodies just found a grave"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 252140.0,
      "end_time": 253947.0,
      "text": "right here in my esophagus."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 254413.0,
      "end_time": 255564.0,
      "text": "Our once country,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 255588.0,
      "end_time": 257817.0,
      "text": "all north and south and east and west,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 257841.0,
      "end_time": 260760.0,
      "text": "so restless the Nile couldn&#39;t hold us together,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 260784.0,
      "end_time": 262643.0,
      "text": "and you ask me to summarize."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 263174.0,
      "end_time": 266209.0,
      "text": "They talk about the numbers as if this isn&#39;t still happening,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 266233.0,
      "end_time": 269450.0,
      "text": "as if 500,000 didn&#39;t just die in Syria,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 269474.0,
      "end_time": 272368.0,
      "text": "as if 3,000 aren&#39;t still making their final stand"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 272392.0,
      "end_time": 275556.0,
      "text": "at the bottom of the Mediterranean,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 275580.0,
      "end_time": 280318.0,
      "text": "as if there aren&#39;t entire volumes full of fact sheets about our genocides,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 280343.0,
      "end_time": 282197.0,
      "text": "and now they want me to write one."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 283740.0,
      "end_time": 284237.0,
      "text": "Fact:"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 285703.0,
      "end_time": 287965.0,
      "text": "we never talked over breakfast,"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 287989.0,
      "end_time": 290703.0,
      "text": "because the warplanes would swallow our voices."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 290728.0,
      "end_time": 292306.0,
      "text": "Fact:"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 292330.0,
      "end_time": 294794.0,
      "text": "my grandfather didn&#39;t want to leave home,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 294818.0,
      "end_time": 296847.0,
      "text": "so he died in a war zone."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 297467.0,
      "end_time": 298806.0,
      "text": "Fact:"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 298831.0,
      "end_time": 301906.0,
      "text": "a burning bush without God is just a fire."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 302472.0,
      "end_time": 304657.0,
      "text": "I measure the distance between what I know"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 304682.0,
      "end_time": 306932.0,
      "text": "and what is safe to say on a microphone."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 306956.0,
      "end_time": 309850.0,
      "text": "Do I talk about sorrow? Displacement?"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 309874.0,
      "end_time": 311267.0,
      "text": "Do I mention the violence,"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 311291.0,
      "end_time": 313971.0,
      "text": "how it&#39;s never as simple as what you see on TV,"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 313995.0,
      "end_time": 317813.0,
      "text": "how there are weeks&#39; worth of fear before the camera is on?"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 319474.0,
      "end_time": 322940.0,
      "text": "Do I tell her about our bodies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 322118.0,
      "end_time": 323569.0,
      "text": "how they are 60 percent water,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 323593.0,
      "end_time": 325510.0,
      "text": "but we still burn like driftwood,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 325534.0,
      "end_time": 327416.0,
      "text": "making fuel of our sacrifice?"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 327440.0,
      "end_time": 331548.0,
      "text": "Do I tell her the men died first, mothers forced to watch the slaughter?"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 331572.0,
      "end_time": 333174.0,
      "text": "That they came for our children,"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 333198.0,
      "end_time": 336352.0,
      "text": "scattering them across the continent until our homes sank?"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 336376.0,
      "end_time": 339505.0,
      "text": "That even castles sink at the bite of the bomb?"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 341593.0,
      "end_time": 343460.0,
      "text": "Do I talk about the elderly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 343484.0,
      "end_time": 345119.0,
      "text": "our heroes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 345143.0,
      "end_time": 347753.0,
      "text": "too weak to run, too expensive to shoot,"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 347778.0,
      "end_time": 349161.0,
      "text": "how they would march them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 349185.0,
      "end_time": 351432.0,
      "text": "hands raised, rifles at their backs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 351456.0,
      "end_time": 352612.0,
      "text": "into the fire?"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 352636.0,
      "end_time": 354906.0,
      "text": "How their walking sticks kept the flames alive?"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 354930.0,
      "end_time": 360114.0,
      "text": "It feels too harsh for a bundle of wires and an audience to swallow."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 360138.0,
      "end_time": 361573.0,
      "text": "Too relentless,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 361598.0,
      "end_time": 365457.0,
      "text": "like the valley that filled with the putrid smoke of our deaths."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 365481.0,
      "end_time": 367314.0,
      "text": "Is it better in verse?"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 367934.0,
      "end_time": 370635.0,
      "text": "Can a stanza become a burial shroud?"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 370659.0,
      "end_time": 372490.0,
      "text": "Will it sting less if I say it softly?"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 372514.0,
      "end_time": 374817.0,
      "text": "If you don&#39;t see me cry, will you listen better?"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 374841.0,
      "end_time": 376957.0,
      "text": "Will the pain leave when the microphone does?"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 376981.0,
      "end_time": 380175.0,
      "text": "Why does every word feel as if I&#39;m saying my last?"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 382760.0,
      "end_time": 384243.0,
      "text": "Thirty seconds for the sound bite,"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 384267.0,
      "end_time": 386367.0,
      "text": "and now three minutes for the poem."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 387140.0,
      "end_time": 391204.0,
      "text": "My tongue goes dry the same way we died,"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 391228.0,
      "end_time": 394420.0,
      "text": "becoming ash, having never been coal."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 396131.0,
      "end_time": 398417.0,
      "text": "I feel my left leg go numb,"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 398441.0,
      "end_time": 401298.0,
      "text": "and I realize that I locked my knees,"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 401322.0,
      "end_time": 402910.0,
      "text": "bracing for impact."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 403557.0,
      "end_time": 406581.0,
      "text": "I never wear shoes I can&#39;t run in."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 408150.0,
      "end_time": 409306.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 409808.0,
      "end_time": 415902.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 416667.0,
      "end_time": 420904.0,
      "text": "So, I wanted to leave on a positive note,"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 420928.0,
      "end_time": 424404.0,
      "text": "because that&#39;s the paradox that this life has been:"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 424428.0,
      "end_time": 427428.0,
      "text": "in the places where I learned to cry the most,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 427452.0,
      "end_time": 430768.0,
      "text": "I also learned how to smile after."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 431435.0,
      "end_time": 433942.0,
      "text": "So, here goes."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 436657.0,
      "end_time": 439510.0,
      "text": "\"You Have a Big Imagination"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 440145.0,
      "end_time": 441421.0,
      "text": "or"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 441446.0,
      "end_time": 445820.0,
      "text": "400,000 Ways to Cry.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 446254.0,
      "end_time": 447405.0,
      "text": "For Zeinab."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 448604.0,
      "end_time": 450111.0,
      "text": "I am a sad girl,"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 451145.0,
      "end_time": 453830.0,
      "text": "but my face makes other plans,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 453854.0,
      "end_time": 458676.0,
      "text": "focusing energy on this smile, so as not to waste it on pain."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 458700.0,
      "end_time": 461223.0,
      "text": "The first thing they took was my sleep,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 461247.0,
      "end_time": 463565.0,
      "text": "eyes heavy but wide open,"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 463589.0,
      "end_time": 465613.0,
      "text": "thinking maybe I missed something,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 465637.0,
      "end_time": 467811.0,
      "text": "maybe the cavalry is still coming."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 467835.0,
      "end_time": 469800.0,
      "text": "They didn&#39;t come,"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 469104.0,
      "end_time": 470916.0,
      "text": "so I bought bigger pillows."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 470940.0,
      "end_time": 472243.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 473328.0,
      "end_time": 477320.0,
      "text": "My grandmother could cure anything"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 477560.0,
      "end_time": 479643.0,
      "text": "by talking the life out of it."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 479667.0,
      "end_time": 482931.0,
      "text": "And she said that I could make a thief in a silo laugh"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 482956.0,
      "end_time": 485360.0,
      "text": "in the middle of our raging war."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 485600.0,
      "end_time": 489482.0,
      "text": "War makes a broken marriage bed out of sorrow."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 490180.0,
      "end_time": 492198.0,
      "text": "You want nothing more than to disappear,"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 492223.0,
      "end_time": 495956.0,
      "text": "but your heart can&#39;t salvage enough remnants to leave."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 496668.0,
      "end_time": 498120.0,
      "text": "But joy --"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 498360.0,
      "end_time": 502363.0,
      "text": "joy is the armor we carried across the borders of our broken homeland."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 504507.0,
      "end_time": 508590.0,
      "text": "A hasty mix of stories and faces"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 508830.0,
      "end_time": 510907.0,
      "text": "that lasts long after the flavor is gone."
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 511838.0,
      "end_time": 515748.0,
      "text": "A muscle memory that overcomes even the most bitter of times,"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 515772.00000000006,
      "end_time": 520321.00000000006,
      "text": "my memory is spotted with days of laughing until I cried,"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 520345.0,
      "end_time": 521980.0,
      "text": "or crying until I laughed."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 522400.0,
      "end_time": 525973.0,
      "text": "Laughter and tears are both involuntary human reactions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 525997.0,
      "end_time": 529170.0,
      "text": "testaments to our capacity for expression."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 529194.0,
      "end_time": 531260.0,
      "text": "So allow me to express"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 531510.0,
      "end_time": 532741.0,
      "text": "that if I make you laugh,"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 532765.0,
      "end_time": 534843.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s usually on purpose."
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 534868.0,
      "end_time": 536595.0,
      "text": "And if I make you cry,"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 536619.0,
      "end_time": 538598.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ll still think you are beautiful."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 539870.0,
      "end_time": 541782.0,
      "text": "This is for my cousin Zeinab,"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 542516.0,
      "end_time": 545530.0,
      "text": "bedridden on a random afternoon."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 545951.0,
      "end_time": 549977.0,
      "text": "I hadn&#39;t seen her since the last time we were in Sudan together,"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 550100.0,
      "end_time": 553954.0,
      "text": "and there I was at her hospital bedside"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 553979.0,
      "end_time": 557337.0,
      "text": "in a 400-year-old building in France."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 558867.0,
      "end_time": 561112.0,
      "text": "Zeinab wanted to hear poems."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 561999.0,
      "end_time": 566490.0,
      "text": "Suddenly, English, Arabic and French were not enough."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 566730.0,
      "end_time": 569459.0,
      "text": "Every word I knew became empty noise,"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 569484.0,
      "end_time": 571758.0,
      "text": "and Zeinab said, \"Well, get on with it.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 571782.0,
      "end_time": 572859.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 572883.0,
      "end_time": 576450.0,
      "text": "And I read her everything that I could,"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 576690.0,
      "end_time": 577405.0,
      "text": "and we laughed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 577429.0,
      "end_time": 578584.0,
      "text": "and we loved it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 578609.0,
      "end_time": 582584.0,
      "text": "and it was the most important stage that I&#39;ve ever stood on,"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 582608.0,
      "end_time": 584419.0,
      "text": "surrounded by family,"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 584443.0,
      "end_time": 589218.0,
      "text": "by remnants of a people who were given as a dowry to a relentless war"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 589243.0,
      "end_time": 592699.0,
      "text": "but still managed to make pearls of this life;"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 592723.0,
      "end_time": 596439.0,
      "text": "by the ones who taught me to not only laugh,"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 596463.0,
      "end_time": 599333.0,
      "text": "but to live in the face of death;"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 599357.0,
      "end_time": 601762.0,
      "text": "who placed their hands across the sky,"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 601787.0,
      "end_time": 605154.0,
      "text": "measuring the distance to the sun and saying, \"Smile;"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 605178.0,
      "end_time": 606833.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m gonna meet you there.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 607618.0,
      "end_time": 609198.0,
      "text": "And for Zeinab --"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 609942.0,
      "end_time": 613513.0,
      "text": "Zeinab, who taught me love in a place like France,"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 614244.0,
      "end_time": 618809.0,
      "text": "Zeinab, who wanted to he.ar poems on her deathbed --"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 620291.0,
      "end_time": 622714.0,
      "text": "Dilated fibromyalgia."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 623603.0,
      "end_time": 625835.0,
      "text": "Her heart muscles expanded"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 626758.0,
      "end_time": 628359.0,
      "text": "until they couldn&#39;t function."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 629100.0,
      "end_time": 632883.0,
      "text": "And she held me, and she made me feel like gold."
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 632907.0,
      "end_time": 634452.0,
      "text": "And I said, \"Zeinab,"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 635301.0,
      "end_time": 638821.0,
      "text": "isn&#39;t it strange that your only problem"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 638845.0,
      "end_time": 641729.0,
      "text": "is that your heart was too big?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 644240.0,
      "end_time": 645439.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 645463.0,
      "end_time": 650247.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}